<TITLE> Bangladeshi tipped best at HK BioCamp </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 2 (bdnews24.com)-A Bangladeshi student was awarded for being one of the most outstanding team players at Novartis International Biotechnology Camp, or BioCamp-2009 in Hongkong. Rashidul Hasan, an IBA student of Dhaka University, won the distinction in the gala, said a press release of Novartis (Bangladesh) Ltd on Sunday. Rashidul and another student Kazi Ali Tahzeeb from the same institute represented Bangladesh in the BioCamp. Leading biotechnology experts and 55 selected postgraduate students from top universities worldwide joined the camp held during last October 24 to 27. Headquartered in Basel, Switzerland, Novartis Group companies employ more than 100,000 people and operate in over 140 countries around the world. Novartis has manufacturing and marketing operation in the areas of research, off patent branded generic (Sandoz), and animal health in Bangladesh since 1973. The company is also a leading pharmaceutical products exporter from Bangladesh.
